%N A397183 a(n) = A317105(n)/2.
%C A397183 This is a finite sequence, the last term being a(3722) = 3540.
%C A397183 This acts as a bridge between a (1,3) leaper moving on the square spiral (see A317105) and on a diagonal spiral (see A329022).
%C A397183 Also, although A317107 gives the complement of A317105, it conceals a somewhat surprising property of the present sequence, which is that, although finite, it contains every number from 0 to 2929.
